    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1900-01-10T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1900-01-10T00:00:00-05:00" n="669"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d669">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Toomey</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Hay</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">New York</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1900-01-10">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 10, 1900</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Please note seized flour was sold by us delivered Delagoa Bay, therefore our
                    property until obligation delivery fulfilled irrespective drafts made against
                    same.</p>
                <p>Some drafts already returned unpaid, leaving flour on our hands in critical
                    position, even if released by British Government.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">A. J. Toomey</hi>, <hi rend="italic">President.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
